TITLE: House to vote on same-sex marriage protections in response to Supreme Court Roe ruling
SUMMARY: The bill is a direct reaction to the Supreme Court's ruling striking down Roe v. Wade and overturning longstanding federal abortion rights.

TITLE: Biden to sign executive order aiming to deter taking of U.S. hostages, wrongful detentions
SUMMARY: The executive order comes as the Biden administration works to release WNBA star Brittney Griner from a Russian prison.

TITLE: Biden could declare a public health emergency to expand abortion access, but it would face a tremendous legal fight
SUMMARY: The nation's leading reproductive rights groups are calling for the White House to use every power at its disposal to defend access to abortion.

TITLE: DOJ won't prosecute group linked to Colbert's 'The Late Show' after unlawful entry arrests, Capitol police say
SUMMARY: The group of nine people associated with CBS' "The Late Show With Stephen Colbert" were arrested on unlawful entry charges last month.

TITLE: Vice President Kamala Harris compares Supreme Court abortion ruling to slavery: 'Claiming ownership over human bodies'
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court ruling that overturned Roe v. Wade is expected to lead to abortion being banned or severely restricted in nearly half the United States.

TITLE: Pulitzer board rejects Trump's calls to revoke prizes for reporting on Russian election meddling
SUMMARY: The Pulitzer board said that two investigations affirmed the prize-winning reporting on Russia's meddling in the election and its links to Trump's campaign.

TITLE: Harris, Newsom engage with donors as possible 2024 bids loom if Biden doesn't run
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden says he's running for reelection in 2024. That hasn't stopped his allies from apparent moves to prepare for a run themselves.

TITLE: GOP Georgia Rep. Jody Hice moves to quash subpoena from Trump election-meddling grand jury
SUMMARY: The same Georgia grand jury was known to have subpoenaed other Trump allies, among them Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C.

TITLE: Feds say 2 NY residents used Trump fundraiser, photo in $27 million investment scam
SUMMARY: Prosecutors said the defendants leveraged their attendance at a 2017 Donald Trump fundraiser in a massive investment fraud scheme.

TITLE: Ivana Trump died from accident, blunt impact injuries, New York City medical examiner rules
SUMMARY: The New York Attorney General's Office postponed depositions of Donald Trump, Donald Trump Jr. and Ivanka Trump in light of Ivana's death.

TITLE: Joe Manchin raises over $1 million from donors including Patriots owner, Wall Street execs, energy giants
SUMMARY: Joe Manchin raised over $1 million from Bob Kraft, Wall Street titans and energy giants as he stalls his own party's agenda.

TITLE: Biden's effort to tout progress in Saudi relationship overshadowed by Khashoggi killing
SUMMARY: Biden fist-bumped Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, and then hours later condemned his regime for the murder of journalist Jamal Khashoggi.

TITLE: Maryland gubernatorial candidate Wes Moore sets fundraiser plan with Spike Lee in Martha's Vineyard
SUMMARY: Maryland gubernatorial candidate Wes Moore has set a private fundraiser at the Martha's Vineyard home of Oscar-winning filmmaker Spike Lee.

TITLE: Biden said he raised murder of Jamal Khashoggi with Saudi leaders after MBS fist bump
SUMMARY: President Biden faces criticism for visiting Saudi Arabia. Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman is suspected of ordering the killing of Jamal Khashoggi.

TITLE: Depositions of Trump and two children delayed due to Ivana Trump's death, NY AG says
SUMMARY: Trump, Donald Trump Jr. and Ivanka Trump were scheduled to testify as part of NY AG Letitia James' civil investigation into the Trump Organization.

TITLE: Biden arrives in Saudi Arabia a 'much diminished president,' the kingdom's former intel chief says
SUMMARY: Saudi Arabia's former intelligence chief has branded U.S. President Joe Biden a "much diminished president" as Biden arrives in Jeddah to discuss oil production, defense and human rights.

TITLE: Senate could proceed on slimmer, chip-focused China competitiveness bill next week
SUMMARY: Lawmakers hope to send chip-funding legislation to President Joe Biden before Congress goes on its annual recess next month.

TITLE: Republican attorneys general to host private retreat for corporate donors at swanky Palm Beach resort
SUMMARY: CNBC obtained a list of nearly 20 corporations and trade groups that RSVP'd to attend a retreat at the Breakers resort hosted by Republican attorneys general.

TITLE: Texas sues to block Biden from requiring doctors to provide abortions in medical emergencies
SUMMARY: Three days before the Texas lawsuit, HHS Secretary Xavier Becerra told hospitals and physicians they have to provide abortions in medical emergencies.

TITLE: Jan. 6 panel's next hearing will focus on Trump's hourslong failure to stop the Capitol riot
SUMMARY: Committee members said the next hearing will focus on former President Donald Trump's "supreme dereliction of duty" during the invasion.

TITLE: A second wave of Russians is fleeing Putin's regime
SUMMARY: 37-year-old Vladimir is one of a number of Russians who took time to get their affairs in order, but are now leaving the country.

TITLE: Judge denies trial delay for former Trump aide Steven Bannon on Jan.6 contempt of Congress charges
SUMMARY: Bannon's attorneys had argued that the publicity ahead of the trial raised the risk of prejudicing the jury against him.

TITLE: Sen. Lindsey Graham asks federal judge to quash subpoena from Georgia grand jury probing Trump election meddling
SUMMARY: A Georgia grand jury is investigating if ex-President Donald Trump broke the law in efforts to get the state to reverse its election of President Joe Biden.

TITLE: Former Trump aide Steve Bannon cites Jan. 6 Capitol riot hearing in seeking delay of criminal contempt trial
SUMMARY: Former Trump White House advisor Steven Bannon previously lost a bid to delay his contempt trial, which relates to Jan. 6 Capitol riot panel subpoenas.

TITLE: U.S. calls on Russia to halt forced deportations of Ukrainians, citing war crimes
SUMMARY: The Kremlin has previously denied all claims that its forces target and kill civilians.

TITLE: Pharmacies risk violating civil rights laws if they deny access to drugs that can be used for abortion, HHS says
SUMMARY: Medication used to terminate pregnancies has become a flashpoint between the Biden administration and states who are banning abortion.

TITLE: Trump accused of possible witnesses tampering: Here are the highlights from the latest Jan. 6 committee hearing
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump was accused of witness tampering during the latest Jan. 6 committee hearing.

TITLE: Ex-Trump campaign manager Brad Parscale said Trump’s ‘civil war' rhetoric 'killed someone' on Jan. 6
SUMMARY: The House panel probing the riot showed screenshots of texts between Parscale and Trump surrogate Katrina Pierson from the evening of the riot.

TITLE: Jan. 6 committee notifies DOJ that Trump tried tampering with one of its witnesses, Cheney says
SUMMARY: The Jan. 6 committee said it notified the Department of Justice of Donald Trump trying to tamper with one of its witnesses.

TITLE: Elon Musk says it's time for Trump to 'sail into the sunset'
SUMMARY: Over the weekend, Trump called Elon Musk a "bull---- artist" claiming that Musk said he voted for Trump in previous conversations between the two men.
